dcterms:description: The CIFAR-100 dataset consists of 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Patryk Chrabaszcz
Ilya Loshchilov
Frank Hutter
dcterms:description: Tiny ImageNet is a downsampled variant of ImageNet, consisting of 100,000 images across 200 classes, each image being 64x64 pixels. It serves as an alternative to the CIFAR datasets for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Tiny ImageNet
